754
00:52:54,938 --> 00:52:59,568
Claire? Hi, Listen,
When was the last time you spoke to Dad?

755
00:53:01,903 --> 00:53:04,072
Tuesday? Oh, God,

756
00:53:04,906 --> 00:53:07,909
It's fine, It's just that
I normally talk to him every day,

757
00:53:07,951 --> 00:53:11,163
and I haven't been able
to get ahold of him,

758
00:53:11,246 --> 00:53:15,083
Well, I'm glad that
you're sure everything's fine,

759
00:53:15,125 --> 00:53:18,420
I feel much more comfortable,
Thank you,

760
00:53:19,504 --> 00:53:23,550
What could have happened?
I mean, he could've had a car accident,

761
00:53:23,633 --> 00:53:26,094
He could've fallen and broken his hip,

762
00:53:26,136 --> 00:53:30,598
He could be running naked
down the Midway for all I know,

763
00:53:31,933 --> 00:53:35,437
Yes, Claire, I know
that you care about Dad,

764
00:53:35,520 --> 00:53:41,526
Yeah, as much as me, OK,
Now can I please get off the phone?

765
00:54:14,642 --> 00:54:16,310
Dad?

766
00:54:20,481 --> 00:54:22,441
Hello!

767
00:54:39,959 --> 00:54:41,627
Dad?

768
00:54:58,602 --> 00:54:59,728
Dad!

769
00:55:34,346 --> 00:55:36,723
Dad?

770
00:55:36,765 --> 00:55:38,851
Catherine, hi,
What a surprise,

771
00:55:39,601 --> 00:55:42,688
- What are you doing out here?
- I'm thinking,

772
00:55:42,771 --> 00:55:44,606
Writing,

773
00:55:44,690 --> 00:55:47,401
It's 30 degrees,
